<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="266" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[121,1089,147,1075]" pageId="13" pageNumber="266">
Remarks. Initially the holotype could not be found in the 
<collectionCode box="[803,879,841,867]" collectionName="Brazil, Sao Paulo, Sao Paulo, Museu de Zoologia da Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="13" pageNumber="266">MZSP</collectionCode>
collection as indicated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Martin, C. H." box="[224,393,875,902]" firstAuthor="Martin" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="13" pageNumber="266" pagination="189 - 193" part="77" refId="ref21707" refString="Martin, C. H. (1975) Review of the genus Schildia Aldrich (Diptera: Leptogastridae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 77: 189 - 193." title="Review of the genus Schildia Aldrich (Diptera: Leptogastridae)" type="journal article" year="1975">Martin (1975)</bibRefCitation>
, but was recovered in the 
<collectionCode box="[692,761,876,902]" collectionName="USA, Florida, Gainesville, Division of Plant Industry, Florida State Collection of Arthropods" pageId="13" pageNumber="266">FSCA</collectionCode>
among other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1862" box="[923,1089,876,902]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="266" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Leptogastrinae">Leptogastrinae</taxonomicName>
type specimens. The 
<collectionCode box="[361,430,910,936]" collectionName="USA, Florida, Gainesville, Division of Plant Industry, Florida State Collection of Arthropods" pageId="13" pageNumber="266">FSCA</collectionCode>
purchased Charles H. Martin’s private collection after he passed away. The holotype was not collected in 
<date box="[672,857,945,971]" pageId="13" pageNumber="266" value="1940-12">December 1940</date>
as stated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Martin, C. H." firstAuthor="Martin" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="13" pageNumber="266" pagination="189 - 193" part="77" refId="ref21707" refString="Martin, C. H. (1975) Review of the genus Schildia Aldrich (Diptera: Leptogastridae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 77: 189 - 193." title="Review of the genus Schildia Aldrich (Diptera: Leptogastridae)" type="journal article" year="1975">Martin (1975)</bibRefCitation>
in his original description, but in 
<date box="[581,726,980,1006]" pageId="13" pageNumber="266" value="1939-08">August 1939</date>
as clearly indicated on the label. This is the only Neotropical species found in xeric shrub lands and not in tropical or subtropical broad leafed forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
